latestIgtvVideos.title: JAIN MUTTER PANEER
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So here is the quick recipe of my favourite sabzi:
INGREDIENTS:
1 medium sized capsicum
4 medium sized tomatoes
water for boiling
7-8 cashewnuts
1 tbsp of fresh cream/ malai
2 tbsp of ghee
1 tbsp of oil
1 tsp of cumin seeds
1tsp of asafoetida
1 tbsp of ginger-chilly paste
1 cup of green peas
100 gms of paneer
1 tbsp of red chilly powder
1 tsp of tumeric powder
1 tsp of coriander powder
(secret masala of my recipe
is pav bhaji masala which makes it tastes like the restaurant one)
salt as per taste
Method:
1.Take tomatoes and capsicum in a vessel and boil it for 2-3 mins and grind them into puree.
2.Take cashews and crush them afterwards put cream/ malai and grind again and make a medium thick paste of it.
3. Take a pan add ghee , cumin seeds and asafoetida with ginger chilly paste and stir for 1 min.
4. Add the puree to it and cook for 5-6 mins to cook the puree properly.
5. Add all the remaining spices mentioned above with  cashew paste, Paneer and peas and lastly add salt which will add the taste the dish.
6. Serve hot and eat quickly before it gets cold.

latestIgtvVideos.title: APPAM CAKE POPS
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here is the easy-pizzy recipe of APPAM CAKE POPS♥
For making the batter:
1 cup of refined flour
¾ cup of castor sugar
1 tsp of baking powder
½ tsp of baking soda
3 tbsp of cocoa powder
½ cup of curd
½ cup of oil
1 tsp of vanilla essence
Mix all the dry ingredients first then mix oil and curd together in a separate bowl.
Furthermore, add dry and wet ingredients. 
Afterwards, add ½ cup of milk and whisk everything together and pour them into the Appam pan and let cook for 2 mins from both sides.
For making choco sauce:
2 tbsp of sugar
2 tbsp of cocoa powder
½ cup of milk
1 tsp of fresh cream
Mix all in a pan and whisk on low heat.
Serve the appam in a plate and drizzle the sauce over it.

latestIgtvVideos.title: CHOCOLATE DONUTS🍩
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
NO YEAST DONUTS...Can you believe this?
But its true that they are really fluffy without yeast too.
so what are you waiting for..try them out and let me know how they were!!!
As I said will share the recipe of lovely chocolatw donuts so here it is:
FOR MAKING THE DOUGH
1¼ cup of refined flour
¼ cup of castor sugar
¼ tsp of baking powder
¼ tsp of baking soda
1 tsp of vinegar
Pinch of salt
¼ cup of milk
1 tsp of ghee
Mix all the ingredients well and knead the dough for 10 mins and make a soft dough. And let it rest for 1 hour with brushing some ghee on the top.
Then knead again for 15 secs and roll it a slightly thicker on the platform by sprinkling some flour below the dough and cut it with a cookie cutter or simply any lid.
Fry it until golden brown on low flame.
TIP: DO NOT TURN THE FLAME HIGH AS IT WILL SHOW THAT IT IS GOLDEN BUT WON'T BE COOKED FROM INSIDE.
FOR MAKING CHOCOLATE SAUCE:
4 tsp of cocoa powder
4 tsp of sugar
¼ cup of milk
Mixx all these in a pan and add some fresh cream or malai for smooth texture.
Then dip the donut into the sauce. 
And voilà, it is ready to be attacked by you;)

latestIgtvVideos.title: MINI FALAFEL BURGER
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I have made this fusion recipe with all the ingredients that are easily available at home.
FOLLOW @obessed_with_food_and_art
so you keep up with all my recipes.
Use #obsesedwithfoodandart
to get featured.
Here is the recipe of this yummy dish:
MINI FALAFEL BURGERS
For making falafel:
100gms of chickpeas (soaked for 3-4hours) 
1 tbsp of chilly paste
1tsp of suth powder
1tbsp of coriander powder
1 tsp of cumin powder
1tbsp of chilly powder
½tsp of crushed pepper
salt as per taste
1tbsp of lemon juice
4-5 diced capsicum
 1 tbsp of crushed peanuts 
1tbsp of rice flour
Take all the ingredients in a mixer jar and blendly them roughly
Then add ¼tsp of baking soda 
Then make small balls out of the mixture with wet hands and fry them
For making white sauce:
Take 2 tbsp of ghee
1 tbsp of refined flour in a pan and stir for 2mins 
Then add some milk slowly and stir continuously to avoid lumps.
Stir till it gets thicken up and then add 1tbsp of fresh malai and some salt, pepper and chilly flakes to add some spice to the sauce.
For making pudina chutney
Take some mint leaves
1-2 green chillies 
1tbsp of chana powder
Salt as per taste
Pink salt as per taste
Water for mixing
1 tsp of chaat masala
1 tsp of lemon juice 
Then take all the ingredients and crush them into chutney.
For making burger
Take normal wheat chapati and cut them in small circles with the help of the cutter. 
For plating:
Take the chapati apply some white sauce over it and then keep the falafel and cover it with pudina chutney applied on chapati  again and insert a toothpick for stand. 
And your mini falafel burgers are ready to eat!!!
